# Project Structure Guide

This project is organized as follows:

- The main application code is in the `app/` directory. Pages and routes are nested within, such as `app/share/[id]/` for dynamic share pages.
- Reusable UI components are in `components/ui/`.
- Custom React hooks are in the `hooks/` directory.
- Utility and helper functions are in `lib/`.
- Static assets are in `public/`.
- Global styles are in `styles/`.
- Project configuration files include:
  - [next.config.mjs](mdc:next.config.mjs) for Next.js configuration
  - [tailwind.config.ts](mdc:tailwind.config.ts) for Tailwind CSS setup
  - [postcss.config.mjs](mdc:postcss.config.mjs) for PostCSS
  - [tsconfig.json](mdc:tsconfig.json) for TypeScript
  - [package.json](mdc:package.json) and [pnpm-lock.yaml](mdc:pnpm-lock.yaml) for dependencies
- The [README.md](mdc:README.md) provides an overview and setup instructions.

Follow this structure to locate files and understand the organization of the codebase.
